<li id="ref-MPT:2023">Metcalfe, George, Francesco Paoli, and
Constantine Tsinakis, 2023, <em>Residuated Structures in Algebra and
Logic</em> (Mathematical Surveys and Monographs 277), Providence, RI:
American Mathematical Society. doi:10.1090/surv/277</li>

<li id="ref-meyer1989abelian">Meyer, Robert K. and John K. Slaney,
1989, &ldquo;Abelian Logic (from A to Z)&rdquo;, in <em>Paraconsistent
Logic: Essays on the Inconsistent</em> (Analytica), Graham Priest,
Richard Sylvan, and Jean Norman (eds), M&uuml;nchen/Hamden, CT:
Philosophia, 245&ndash;288.</li>

<li id="ref-Mostowski:1957">Mostowski, Andrzej, 1957, &ldquo;On a
Generalization of Quantifiers&rdquo;, <em>Fundamenta
Mathematicae</em>, 44(1): 12&ndash;36.</li>

<li id="ref-Mostowski:1961">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1961,
&ldquo;Axiomatizability of Some Many Valued Predicate Calculi&rdquo;,
<em>Fundamenta Mathematicae</em>, 50(2): 165&ndash;190.</li>

<li id="ref-Mundici:1987">Mundici, Daniele, 1987,
&ldquo;Satisfiability in Many-Valued Sentential Logic is
NP-Complete&rdquo;, <em>Theoretical Computer Science</em>,
52(1&ndash;2): 145&ndash;153. doi:10.1016/0304-3975(87)90083-1</li>

<li id="ref-OdintsovWansing:2010">Odintsov, Sergei P. and Heinrich
Wansing, 2010, &ldquo;Modal Logics with Belnapian Truth Values&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Applied Non-Classical Logics</em>, 20(3):
279&ndash;301.</li>

<li id="ref-pailos2024pure">Pailos, Federico, 2024, &ldquo;On All Pure
Three-Valued Logics&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Logic and Computation</em>,
34(1): 161&ndash;179. doi:10.1093/logcom/exac087</li>

<li id="ref-paoli2024sequent">Paoli, Francesco and Adam P&#345;enosil,
2024, &ldquo;Sequent Calculi for First-Order ST&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Philosophical Logic</em>, 53(5): 1291&ndash;1320.
doi:10.1007/s10992-024-09766-3</li>

<li id="ref-Pelletier-Martin:1990">Pelletier, Francis Jeffry and
Norman M. Martin, 1990, &ldquo;Post&rsquo;s Functional Completeness
Theorem&rdquo;, <em>Notre Dame Journal of Formal Logic</em>, 31(3):
462&ndash;475. doi:10.1305/ndjfl/1093635508</li>

<li id="ref-peters1979truth">Peters, Stanley, 1979, &ldquo;A
Truth-Conditional Formulation of Karttunen&rsquo;s Account of
Presupposition&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>, 40(2): 301&ndash;316.
doi:10.1007/BF00485682</li>

<li id="ref-PietzRivieccio:2013">Pietz, Andreas and Umberto Rivieccio,
2013, &ldquo;Nothing but the Truth&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Philosophical Logic</em>, 42(1): 125&ndash;135.
doi:10.1007/s10992-011-9215-1</li>

<li id="ref-porter2022supervaluations">Porter, Brian, 2022,
&ldquo;Supervaluations and the Strict-Tolerant Hierarchy&rdquo;,
<em>Journal of Philosophical Logic</em>, 51(6): 1367&ndash;1386.
doi:10.1007/s10992-021-09624-6</li>

<li id="ref-Post:1921">Post, Emil Leon, 1921, &ldquo;Introduction to a
General Theory of Elementary Propositions&rdquo;, <em>American Journal
of Mathematics</em>, 43(3): 163&ndash;185. doi:10.2307/2370324</li>

<li id="ref-Post:1941">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1941, <em>The Two-Valued
Iterative Systems of Mathematical Logic</em> (Annals of Mathematics
Studies 5), Princeton, NJ: Princeton University Press.
doi:10.1515/9781400882366</li>

<li id="ref-Prenosil:2023">P&#345;enosil, Adam, 2023, &ldquo;Logics of
Upsets of De Morgan Lattices&rdquo;, <em>Mathematical Logic
Quarterly</em>, 69(4): 419&ndash;445. doi:10.1002/malq.202100076</li>

<li id="ref-Priest:1979">Priest, Graham, 1979, &ldquo;The Logic of
Paradox&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Philosophical Logic</em>, 8(1):
219&ndash;241. doi:10.1007/BF00258428</li>

<li id="ref-Raftery:2013">Raftery, James G., 2013,
&ldquo;Inconsistency Lemmas in Algebraic Logic&rdquo;,
<em>Mathematical Logic Quarterly</em>, 59(6): 393&ndash;406.
doi:10.1002/malq.201200020</li>

<li id="ref-Rautenberg:1981">Rautenberg, Wolfgang, 1981,
&ldquo;2-Element Matrices&rdquo;, <em>Studia Logica</em>, 40(4):
315&ndash;353. doi:10.1007/BF00401653</li>

<li id="ref-reichenbach1935wahr">Reichenbach, Hans, 1935,
<em>Wahrscheinlichkeitslehre: eine Untersuchung &uuml;ber die
logischen und mathematischen Grundlagen der
Wahrscheinlichkeitsrechnung</em>, Leiden: A. W. Sijthoff&rsquo;s
uitgeversmaatschappij n.v.</li>

<li id="ref-reichenbach1944philosophic">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1944,
<em>Philosophic Foundations of Quantum Mechanics</em>, Berkeley and
Los Angeles: University of California press.</li>

<li id="ref-rescher:quasi:1962">Rescher, Nicholas, 1962,
&ldquo;Quasi-Truth-Functional Systems of Propositional Logic&rdquo;,
<em>The Journal of Symbolic Logic</em>, 27(1): 1&ndash;10.
doi:10.2307/2963674</li>

<li id="ref-Ripley2012">Ripley, Ellie, 2012, &ldquo;Conservatively
Extending Classical Logic with Transparent Truth&rdquo;, <em>The
Review of Symbolic Logic</em>, 5(2): 354&ndash;378.
doi:10.1017/S1755020312000056</li>

<li id="ref-ripley2013sorting">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2013,
&ldquo;Sorting out the Sorites&rdquo;, in <em>Paraconsistency: Logic
and Applications</em> (Logic, Epistemology and the Unity of Science
26), Koji Tanaka, Francesco Berto, Edwin Mares, and Francesco Paoli
(eds), Dordrecht/New York: Springer, 329&ndash;348.
doi:10.1007/978-94-007-4438-7_18</li>

<li id="ref-Rivieccio:2012">Rivieccio, Umberto, 2012, &ldquo;An
Infinity of Super-Belnap Logics&rdquo;, <em>Journal of Applied
Non-Classical Logics</em>, 22(4): 319&ndash;335.
doi:10.1080/11663081.2012.737154</li>

<li id="ref-RodriguezVidal:2021">Rodriguez, Ricardo Oscar and Amanda
Vidal, 2021, &ldquo;Axiomatization of Crisp G&ouml;del Modal
Logic&rdquo;, <em>Studia Logica</em>, 109(2): 367&ndash;395.
doi:10.1007/s11225-020-09910-5</li>

<li id="ref-Rose:1952">Rose, Alan, 1952, &ldquo;The Degree of
Completeness of the \(m\)-Valued &#321;ukasiewicz Propositional
Calculus&rdquo;, <em>Journal of the London Mathematical Society</em>,
s1-27(1), Oxford University Press: 92&ndash;102.
doi:10.1112/jlms/s1-27.1.92</li>

<li id="ref-Rose-Rosser:1958">Rose, Alan and J. Barkley Rosser, 1958,
&ldquo;Fragments of Many-Valued Statement Calculi&rdquo;,
<em>Transactions of the American Mathematical Society</em>, 87(1):
1&ndash;53. doi:10.1090/S0002-9947-1958-0094299-1</li>

<li id="ref-Rosser-Turquette:1945">Rosser, J. Barkley and Atwell R.
Turquette, 1945, &ldquo;Axiom Schemes for \(m\)-Valued Propositions
Calculi&rdquo;, <em>The Journal of Symbolic Logic</em>, 10(3):
61&ndash;82. doi:10.2307/2267026</li>

<li id="ref-Rosser-Turquette:1952">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1952,
<em>Many-Valued Logics</em> (Studies in Logic and the Foundations of
Mathematics 7), Amsterdam: North-Holland.</li>

<li id="ref-Rumfitt:2000">Rumfitt, Ian, 2000, &ldquo;&lsquo;Yes&rsquo;
and &lsquo;No&rsquo;&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>, 109(436): 781&ndash;823.
doi:10.1093/mind/109.436.781</li>

<li id="ref-Scarpellini:1962">Scarpellini, Bruno, 1962, &ldquo;Die
nichtaxiomatisierbarkeit des unendlichwertigen
Pr&auml;dikatenkalk&uuml;ls von &#321;ukasiewicz&rdquo;, <em>The
