&ldquo;A Criterion of Fullness of Many-Valued Systems of Propositional
Logic&rdquo;, <em>Studia Logica</em>, 30(1): 153&ndash;157.
doi:10.1007/BF02120845</li>

<li id="ref-Smith:2008">Smith, Nicholas J. J., 2008, <em>Vagueness and
Degrees of Truth</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.
doi:10.1093/acprof:oso/9780199233007.001.0001</li>

<li id="ref-spector2025presup">Spector, Benjamin, forthcoming,
&ldquo;Trivalent Logic and Presuppositions&rdquo;, in
 <a href="#ER2025">&Eacute;gr&eacute; and Rossi forthcoming</a>,
 255&ndash;317.</li>

<li id="ref-Statman:1979">Statman, Richard, 1979,
&ldquo;Intuitionistic Propositional Logic Is Polynomial-Space
Complete&rdquo;, <em>Theoretical Computer Science</em>, 9(1):
67&ndash;72. doi:10.1016/0304-3975(79)90006-9</li>

<li id="ref-Suszko:1975">Suszko, Roman, 1975, &ldquo;Remarks on
&#321;ukasiewicz&rsquo;s Three-Valued Logic&rdquo;, <em>Bulletin of
the Section of Logic</em>, 4(3):87&ndash;90.</li>

<li id="ref-Suszko:1977">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1977, &ldquo;The
Fregean Axiom and Polish Mathematical Logic in the 1920s&rdquo;,
