<li id="ref-Thomason1970">Thomason, Richmond H., 1970,
&ldquo;Indeterminist Time and Truth-Value Gaps&rdquo;,
<em>Theoria</em>, 36(3): 264&ndash;281.
doi:10.1111/j.1755-2567.1970.tb00427.x</li>

<li id="ref-thomason1972sortal">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1972, &ldquo;A
Semantic Theory of Sortal Incorrectness&rdquo;, <em>Journal of
Philosophical Logic</em>, 1(2): 209&ndash;258.
doi:10.1007/BF00650499</li>

<li id="ref-tye1994sorites">Tye, Michael, 1994, &ldquo;Sorites
Paradoxes and the Semantics of Vagueness&rdquo;, <em>Philosophical
Perspectives</em>, 8: 189&ndash;206. doi:10.2307/2214170</li>

<li id="ref-Urquhart:1999">Urquhart, Alasdair, 1999, &ldquo;The
Complexity of Decision Procedures in Relevance Logic II&rdquo;,
<em>The Journal of Symbolic Logic</em>, 64(4): 1774&ndash;1802.
doi:10.2307/2586811</li>

<li id="ref-fraassen1966singular">Van Fraassen, Bas C., 1966,
&ldquo;Singular Terms, Truth-Value Gaps, and Free Logic&rdquo;,
<em>The Journal of Philosophy</em>, 63(17): 481&ndash;495.
doi:10.2307/2024549</li>

<li id="ref-fraassen1968presupposition">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, Bas C.,
1968, &ldquo;Presupposition, Implication, and Self-Reference&rdquo;,
<em>The Journal of Philosophy</em>, 65(5): 136&ndash;152.
doi:10.2307/2024557</li>

<li id="ref-varzi1994phd">Varzi, Achille C., 1994, <em>Universal
Semantics</em>, PhD thesis, University of Toronto.</li>

<li id="ref-varzi2007supervaluationism">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007,
&ldquo;Supervaluationism and Its Logics&rdquo;, <em>Mind</em>,
116(463): 633&ndash;676. doi:10.1093/mind/fzm633</li>

<li id="ref-Verdee:2021">Verd&eacute;e, Peter, 2021, &ldquo;Obtaining
Infinitely Many Degrees of Inconsistency by Adding a Strictly
Paraconsistent Negation to Classical Logic&rdquo;, <em>Synthese</em>,
198(Suppl. 22): 5415&ndash;5449. doi:10.1007/s11229-020-02638-8</li>

<li id="ref-Vidal:2021">Vidal, Amanda, 2021, &ldquo;On Transitive
Modal Many-Valued Logics&rdquo;, <em>Fuzzy Sets and Systems</em>, 407:
97&ndash;114. doi:10.1016/j.fss.2020.01.011</li>

<li id="ref-Vidal:2022">&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2022,
